# Optional environment overrides for `docker compose up`.
#
# The compose defaults already work on every host platform out of the
# box:
#
#   - amd64 (Linux / Windows / Intel Mac):
#       runs mssql/server:2022-latest natively
#   - Apple Silicon (arm64):
#       still uses mssql/server:2022-latest, transparently emulated by
#       Rosetta 2 (slightly slower first boot but rock-solid)
#
# So you typically don't need this file at all. Copy it to `.env` only
# if you want to opt in to a different image — e.g. the lighter
# (but, in our experience on M-series Macs, much less stable)
# Azure SQL Edge.
#
# Note on Azure SQL Edge: as of mid-2025 the ARM64 build has been
# crashing with SIGABRT during the master-DB upgrade step on M3+ Macs,
# so we no longer recommend it as a default. If you used to have
# `MSSQL_IMAGE=mcr.microsoft.com/azure-sql-edge:latest` set in `.env`
# and you're seeing MSSQL fail to come up, just delete `.env` and run
# `docker compose down -v && docker compose up -d` to fall back to the
# stable defaults.

# MSSQL_IMAGE=mcr.microsoft.com/mssql/server:2022-latest
# DOCKER_PLATFORM=linux/amd64
